articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel said on Sunday that Yemen's Houthis had seized a British-owned and Japanese-operated cargo ship in the southern Red Sea, describing the incident as an "Iranian act of terrorism" with consequences for international maritime security.
articles.title: Israel says Houthis seize ship in Red Sea, no Israelis among owners or crew

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Spanish military officer was arrested with a pistol at a demonstration against an amnesty law which will benefit Catalan separatists involved in a failed 2017 bid for independence, police said on Sunday.
articles.title: Police seize pistol from military officer at Spanish amnesty protest

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Two people were killed when a tree crushed their car as hurricanes with winds reaching 38 metres per second hit several regions in Russia's Siberia on Sunday.
articles.title: Two killed as hurricanes rage in Russia's Siberia

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Parts of the Dominican Republic were on high alert on Sunday for possible landslides and flooding after heavy rains the day before displaced thousands and killed at least nine people.
articles.title: Dominican Republic on alert after deadly floods kill at least nine

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Actor and comedian Russell Brand has been questioned by detectives from London's Metropolitan Police over allegations of historical sex offences, the Times newspaper reported on Sunday.
articles.title: UK police question Russell Brand over sex assault allegations - The Times

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: More than 500 Rohingya refugees originally from Myanmar landed on the shores of Indonesia's Aceh province on Sunday, the fourth wave of arrivals this week, a local UNHCR official said.
articles.title: Hundreds more Rohingya refugees arrive in Indonesia's Aceh

articles.author: Thomas Peter, Yurii Kovalenko
articles.description: A Ukrainian teenager who was taken to Russia from the occupied city of Mariupol during the war and prevented from leaving the country earlier this year returned to Ukraine on Sunday.
articles.title: Ukrainian teen returns to Ukraine after being taken to Russia from occupied Mariupol

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, James Mackenzie
articles.description: Israel prepared on Sunday to expand its offensive against Hamas militants to southern Gaza after air strikes killed dozens of Palestinians, including civilians reported to be sheltering at two schools.
articles.title: Israeli air strikes kill 47 in southern Gaza ahead of offensive against Hamas

articles.author: Anna Tong, Krystal Hu, Jeffrey Dastin
articles.description: (This Nov. 18 story has been refiled to correct the spelling of 'Khosla' in paragraph 6)
articles.title: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman discusses possible return, mulls new AI venture, source says

articles.author: Kylie Maclellan, Andy Bruce
articles.description: British finance minister Jeremy Hunt said on Sunday he would not implement tax cuts that would push up inflation, days before he announces a major budget update that is widely expected to contain reductions in some taxes.
articles.title: Britain's finance minister says he won't implement tax cuts that fuel inflation
